Description: Three fragments of a corroded copper alloy flat blade or arrow-head (?) with a long tang of circular cross-section.
Curator's comments: According to the Museum register, the item, considered as a blade or a chisel, comes form Tell Dafana; maybe ptolemaic and part of a foundation deposit.
Bibliographic references: Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.55, p.76, p.184, pl.26)
